            </form>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>The point is more than a fair one. Of Duke's eight games, the Blue Devils have been able to turn on the cruise control for the second half in six contests. But after three more seemingly harmless nonconference matchups, the road will get much tougher, with No. 13 Texas Tech, ACC play and St. John's on the horizon.</p>
<p>Still, Duke is going to be able to dominate with its offense on most nights. The Blue Devils have—in Barrett and Williamson—two of the 25 best offensive players in the nation among guys used on at least 28 percent of possessions, not to mention an über-efficient point guard in Jones.</p>
<p>The numbers suggest, however, Duke needs start to cleaning things up when it comes to points that are supposed to be, well, free.</p>
<p><em>Hank Tucker contributed reporting.</em></p>
<p><em>Note: This story was updated at 6 p.m. Sunday, Dec. 9 to reflect statistical changes.</em></p>

